			<p>Violence is the occupation of another&#8217;s body against his will, with aggression being the initiation of precisely that.</p>
<p>Private land ownership is control over land acquired by either homesteading unused land or by taking over control of used land from someone else without aggression.</p>
<p>So by definition there&#8217;s no aggression, not even violence, used in the origination of private land ownership.</p>
<p>The only way how you CAN make such a claim would be to redefine the terms I outlined to you above and in fact also in a nicely structured primer to the right &gt;&gt;&gt;</p>
<p>&#8230; which unfortunately would be what is commonly referred to as sophistry and which I hope you&#8217;re not interested in engaging in, my friend.</p>
